arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase IX: Major CE 363 earthquake leads to the collapse of the West Colonnade directly on top of the Hexagonal Pavement and into the West Cryptoporticus. The accumulation of early debris during this phase contains large amounts of architectural elements mixed with fill and sedimentation washed over the east perimeter wall. Some collapse is also seen in the south of the East Triple Colonnade.
